Text.Value: Why, have you anything to hide?
I forgot you existed outside of Vlaakith's gaze, ra'stil. You are very lucky.

EditorData.NodeContext: rah-STILL said in deep, deep sarcasm

Text.Value: I'm sure your Inquisition has better things to do than castigate youths in training.
I would be more concerned than excited.
Be calm, ra'stil. Those standing in truth need not fear Vlaakith's gaze.

EditorData.NodeContext: rah-STILL said in deep, deep sarcasm

Text.Value: Hero. That could be confused for istik sentimentality.
Until the Inquisitor's slayer is found, and destroyed. No sooner.
Forgive me, we have not been visited by an inquisitor in an age. It is an honour.
With your inquisitor gone, what authority do you claim over us?
What do you mean by that?

EditorData.NodeContext: snappy, doesn't get the insult but knows it's an insult

Text.Value: Do you have no leads? I thought you ardents were meant to be our intelligentsia.
No, but he might scour through the whole crèche in his search.
I am not sure you are in a position to reflect on our motivations, vin'iisk.
Hold your tongue, lest I pull it from your skull.
I hear even Silver Sword Voss has been drafted into the search.
I... forgot myself. I apologise, ardent.
Inquisitor or not, we still have a mission. The artefact remains unfound. Focus.
Your latest crop of yanki have been disrespecting their sa'varsh.
Voss? He's just a war myth for sa'varsh to teach the young ones.
Our crèche did not train your inquisitor.
Any word on the search for the artefact, ra'stil?
Do I detect insubordination in your tone, vin'iisk?
No! Kith'rak Voss is a hero.
Is prattling about tremors when you have a duty not defective, vin'iisk?
We have remained undisturbed for an age. What was that rumbling?
Loose words are food for ghaik spies. You should know better.
Your crèche has much to answer for, allowing an inquisitor to be compromised.
I'd have never dreamed of such insubordination.
I am not surprised that this crèche has yet another defect.
With your commanding officer dead, how long will you stay here?
It's an indictment of this entire crèche. It seems your sa'varsh has gotten sloppy.
What should I do if the ch'r'ai takes me in for questioning?

Synopsis: Main guards chatting while on duty. One intelligence officer, one normal Creche Y'llek guard.
